                    <note type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-1153">Bākōs (Bacchus) was one of the most popular
          saints of the Orient. He was a Roman soldier who was martyred shortly before his
            friend <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1153">Sergius</persName> since he refused
          to sacrifice to the Roman gods.</note>
                    <note type="disambiguation">goes with Sergius</note>
